OL,3,CWater firms to increase pay outs to
OL,4,Ccustomers affected by supply problems
OL,6,FMeanwhile households affected by
OL,7,Fflooding inside their homes from
OL,8,Fsewers could receive #2,000 or more,
OL,9,Fcompared to #1,000 under current
OL,10,Frules, the Department for Environment,
OL,11,FFood and Rural Affairs (Defra) said.
OL,13,FSome water companies voluntarily offer
OL,14,Fcompensation to customers who
OL,15,Fexperience interruptions to their
OL,16,Fsupply or other problems, but there is
OL,17,Fno statutory requirement to do so and
OL,18,Frates can vary significantly among
OL,19,Ffirms and location.
