OL,3,CWater firms to increase pay outs to
OL,4,Ccustomers affected by supply problems
OL,6,FUnder the new rules, a compulsory
OL,7,Fpayment of #220 could have been given
OL,8,Fto 600 properties in Bramley, Sussex,
OL,9,Fwho received the 'Do Not Drink' notice
OL,10,Fin May after a fuel leak. At the time,
OL,11,FThames Water offered a #30 voluntary
OL,12,Fpayment.
OL,14,FThose affected by the cryptosporidium
OL,15,Foutbreak in Brixham, Devon, earlier in
OL,16,Fthe year were not entitled to
OL,17,Fcompensation. However, the new
OL,18,Flegislation would mean customers could
OL,19,Fnow receive at least #10 per 24 hours,
OL,20,Fpotentially amounting to more than
OL,21,F#500 for incidents over eight weeks.
